helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Carla Brooks, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/32705 Thank you for contacting the IT Help Desk! Can you open a PDF file outside of Titanium? It sounds like you do not have a default PDF reader set. In Windows 10, you can set a default PDF reader by following these instructions: 1) Click on the Start Menu 2) Search for "Default App Settings" and open the program 3) Scroll down to the bottom and click "Choose default apps by file type" (should be the third option from the bottom) 4) Scroll down until you see ".pdf" as the file type on the left 5) Then click on the program to the right of it (or "Choose a default" if it does not have one) and select the program you want to open PDFs with by default Respectfully, Daniel Griffith (414) 277 7288

helpdesk-ticket.description:
I have been having nothing but problems with Jenzabar all day long. I have been getting kicked off multiple times in the middle of entering invoices. It freezes up on me and now in the middle of posting my largest batch which has the most important checks in it that have to get done before I leave and Tom S leaves in 20 min plus I have to pick up my car that’s in the shop before 6pm, I receive this error message. I don’t know what this means but I don’t need this stress. Sorry, but I’m just at my wit’s end. Here’s the error message I received when trying to post group #8452.
Thank you.
Stacey Gehrke Accounts Payable Specialist Office of Finance Milwaukee School of Engineering Office: (414)277-7128 AP Email: MSOE-AP@msoe.edu<mailto:MSOE-AP@msoe.edu> Web: www.msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body: Tom S. ran a report to see the credits and debits in the batch. It was off by 350. I looked at the transactions and found which invoice was missing the credit or debit row. The second row is added automatically by the system based off of what account numbers are on the transaction. Had Stacey remove that invoice from the batch and add it again, hoping both rows would generate correctly. They did. Had Stacey run another print edit and the batch became postable again. Marking as resolved.

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Greetings,
We lost connectivity to a weather camera placed atop your Library building. When I called the helpdesk earlier it sounded like there was some sort of network maintenance in the library this morning, 8/9, starting at 6:30am. We lost connectivity to the device at about 6:43am. The IP address for the camera is 155.92.176.17.
Were your firewall rules changed, or was the device disconnected during the maintenance?
Thanks, -- NATHAN HELLER IT SUPPORT SPECIALIST WISN TV | HEARST TELEVISION INC (414) 937-3307 | nheller@hearst.com<mailto:nheller@hearst.com>

helpdesk-note.body: Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/32712 Greetings Mr. Heller, I may have (finally) fixed the network address of your camera. We have set the camera to a DHCP Fixed address of 10.203.17.3, meaning that the camera is set to get its address from DHCP, but the DHCP server will always give it that same network address. Since we're using addresses in 10.0.0.0/8, we had to implement Network Address Translation to make your camera accessible over the internet. The new Internet side IP address of your camera will be 155.92.16.8. Please try that out, and let me know if it works. Jared Liebl Network Administrator MSOE 1025 North Broadway Milwaukee WI 53202 414-277-7427 liebl@msoe.edu
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/32712

Greetings Mr. Heller,

I may have (finally) fixed the network address of your camera.

We have set the camera to a DHCP Fixed address of 10.203.17.3, meaning that the camera is set to get its address from DHCP, but the DHCP server will always give it that same network address.

Since we're using addresses in 10.0.0.0/8, we had to implement Network Address Translation to make your camera accessible over the internet.

The new Internet side IP address of your camera will be 155.92.16.8.  Please try that out, and let me know if it works.


Jared Liebl
Network Administrator
MSOE
1025 North Broadway
Milwaukee WI 53202
414-277-7427
liebl@msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body:
Hello Jared,
It looks like we’re still unable to reach it at 155.92.16.8; Are there any firewall rules that might be inhibiting the video traffic. We use the following ports:
HTTP Port 80 SSL Port 443 RTSP Port 554 The traffic to the camera should be originating from 67.52.0.42.
Are you able to ping or reach the camera’s webpage internally? If not, it may be an issue with the camera’s configuration and we will need to send someone out to look at it.
-- NATHAN HELLER IT MANAGER WISN TV | HEARST TELEVISION INC (414) 937-3307 | nheller@hearst.com<mailto:nheller@hearst.com>

To: Heller, Nate <nheller@hearst.com>
Subject: Re: [#INC-32712] Lost connectivity to weather camera
 
Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/32712
 
Greetings Mr. Heller,
 
I may have (finally) fixed the network address of your camera.
 
We have set the camera to a DHCP Fixed address of 10.203.17.3, meaning that the camera is set to get its address from DHCP, but the DHCP server will always give it that same network address.
 
Since we're using addresses in 10.0.0.0/8, we had to implement Network Address Translation to make your camera accessible over the internet.
 
The new Internet side IP address of your camera will be 155.92.16.8.  Please try that out, and let me know if it works.
 
 
Jared Liebl

MSOE

Milwaukee WI 53202

helpdesk-note.body:
Our current sync/web subscription license does not us to distribute the fonts on other computers. We would have to look at purchasing the font from the foundry. When Saj and I talked about this back in November, he opted to go with the closest alternative. I nerded out on fonts and made the following recommendations via email:
Brandon Grotesque:
• Century Gothic – the g is wrong, but the q, b and p are very close. Numbers are very close. Ascend is smaller.
• Gill Sans – the g and numbers are the closest match, but the q, b and p aren’t quite right (the bowl on these letters goes straight into the top/bottom of the stem, not at a curve).
• Calibri – the g is correct, as are the q, b and p. The numbers have more of a curvature on the 6 and 9, 1 has a serif
For Minion Pro:
• Book Antiqua – g, q, p all very close. b is a bit off. Numbers very close.
• Times New Roman – Oldie but goodie. The q, b, g are nearly identical. The j has more of a tail. Numbers nearly identical as well.
• Garamond – Very similar to Book Antiqua, though the numbers aren’t as close.
That said... if other departments are starting to ask for them, perhaps we should revisit this with Saj and Leigh Ann?

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Qualtrech survey request
helpdesk-ticket.description:
We are looking to build a survey to collect info for the upcoming MSOE CommUNITY Fair featuring staff and faculty passions!
I have never built one so please advise what else is needed:
The MSOE CommUNITY Fair is an event that aims to connect students, staff and faculty in an informal setting by showcasing the passions and hobbies that make our community great! By highlighting staff and faculty’s passions, students will be able to meet professionals from outside their academic department and create a larger support circle, which will create a greater sense of community on campus.
Event date: Monday, September 17th, Noon to 2pm in the Kern Field House (Week 3)
RSVP (yes/no) Last name First name Department (drop down with all the departments on campus if possible) Email Select a Category you have an interest in:
* Outdoors: Biking, skiing, rock climbing, etc… * Performance arts: Music, theater, improv, poetry, etc… * Visual arts: Photography, painting, pottery, fashion, clothes making, etc… * Innovation and entrepreneurship: 3D printing, inventions, patents, startup ideas, etc… * Athletics: Playing sports, fan-dom, fantasy leagues, E-sports, etc… * Nerd-con: Gaming, steampunk, sci-fi, anime, etc… * Air and space: NASA, Airplanes, drones, pilots, etc… * Rubber and road: Cars, motorcycles, engines, etc… * Diversity/inclusion: LGBT, veterans, cultural cuisine/traditions/crafts, etc. What hobbies will you be displaying/talking about? (ex; Nick Seidler will be bringing his Dr. Who books and talking about them under the Nerd-con area, Dr. Baumgartner will be talking about his time with NASA, Dr. Howell will bring his bike and talk about cycling) Would you be interested in being a Category lead? (duties would be helping set up and break down ‘booth’, communicating any resources needed to Student Life) Is there a category you think we missed that you would be willing to represent? ____________ Anything else you want us to know/consider?
~ Thank you for completing this survey. You will receive and email with additional event details closer to the date.
Thanks in advance,
Codi Alger Coordinator of Student Programming and Engagement Milwaukee School of Engineering 414.277.7207 Office 414.277.7225 Department alger@msoe.edu<mailto:alger@msoe.edu>

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Moving In
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hi, this is Patrick Walby. I just have a few questions as I'm having trouble finding out some of the details for move in. Firstly, how do I figure out my room assignment and roommate? Secondly, how do I register my vehicle for parking? Thirdly, I would like to change my major from Software Engineer to Mechanical and was wanting to know if that's my job or yours and if that would affect my first trimester classes? Finally, I would like to make sure that my scholarship and grant have been accepted and if any payment is due soon? I'm sorry about the long email but I've been having trouble navigating the website and figuring out some of the things on the to do list you sent me. I hope to hear from you soon.
From, Patrick Walby

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Missing Classroom Climate Survey link
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Good Afternoon,
I spoke with Adi regarding this situation: Earlier this week I was expecting a link from the Classroom Climate system to complete a course evaluation. The instructions state that after week 10 ends, the system will not permit me to submit an evaluation. This deadline is coming up quickly and I would very much like to participate in the course evaluation. I notified Professor Shimek on 8/7, but would also like to follow up with the helpdesk to ensure that this is not a technical issue. To my knowledge, vanselowr@msoe.edu is my primary email, however, when registering for classes my alumni email (ryan.vanselow@alumni.msoe.edu) and my gmail (wyanrv@gmail.com) were used to apply for and exchange information during the graduate school process. I have since checked all three email addresses for a link from the classroom climate system and have not found anything.
attached is a screen shot of the MG-631 instructions for the course evaluation.
Thanks in advance for your help!
Ryan
[cid:c8186354-ccdf-4656-acc7-601654b2b9d7]
Figure 1. taken from Week 10 syllabus

helpdesk-note.body: Hi Ryan Vanselow, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/32754 Thank you for contacting the helpdesk regarding this issue. Class Climate is primarily handled by the Registrars Office. Try to contact them and see what email they have on record for you and what email they sent the survey to. Their number is 414.277.7215 and their email is registrar@msoe.edu. I will be resolving this ticket on IT's end, but if the registrar directs you back to IT, you can reply to this email and the ticket will re-open. Good luck! Respectfully, Amanda Goff 414.277.7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu Helpdesk Summer Hours: Monday-Friday 8 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Saturday-Sunday CLOSED "We are building a culture of exceptional customer service!"

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Spam/Junk filter false positive rate
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Dear IT Department,
I’ve noticed an uptick of false positives of identifying incoming emails as Spam/Junk over the last week or so. Dr. Williams forwarded one of these (below) from our advisory committee member at Rockwell Automation. Could you tune the filter to reduce these errors, or let us know if there is a way that we can train the system that incoming messages like these aren’t spam?
Thank You,
Eric Durant

helpdesk-note.body:
Dr. Durant, If you right-click on an email and select the SPAM menu, you can filter messages for your own account. We generally don't whitelist entire domains due to the increased chance for phishing or SPAM from that domain to reach our end users. The algorithm that finds unwanted email is a global policy included as part of our Microsoft contract. We can fine-tune it further, but we are not using most of the more aggressive features. Please reach out and let us know if you have something specific in mind, but I think you'll find that periodically checking the SPAM folder, and locally whitelisting domains or accounts through your Outlook will address many of these false positives. Thanks, Paul Fabian MSOE Director of IT Services fabian@msoe.edu Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/32850 Dear IT Department,
I’ve noticed an uptick of false positives of identifying incoming emails as Spam/Junk over the last week or so. Dr. Williams forwarded one of these (below) from our advisory committee member at Rockwell Automation. Could you tune the filter to reduce these errors, or let us know if there is a way that we can train the system that incoming messages like these aren’t spam?
Thank You,
Eric Durant

helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello,

Whenever I attempt to log into the webcard service, it gives me a login failed message. I am wondering if the username I need to use is my msoe ID or email, and if the password is the one for my email or the original one given to log onto it.

Thank you,
Joseph Hable

helpdesk-note.body: Hi Joseph Hable, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/32851 Thank you for contacting the IT Help Desk. I am sorry to hear you are having issues logging in. The credentials you would use to log in to webcard.msoe.edu would be your username (your MSOE email address without @msoe.edu) and the password would be the same as the one for your MSOE email. Please let us know if you experience any more issues logging in. Respectfully, Savanah Cleveland Student Manager (414) 277-7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body: Hi Douglas Grabenstetter, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/32922 Please uninstall your current version of global protect by going to control panel, global protect, and then uninstall. The link for installing global protect is http://bit.ly/msoevpn. Please download the 64 bit version for windows! You'll need to login using your MSOE username and password to activate it. If you are still having printing issues after this, please go search for and open device manager, go to print queues, uninstall the follow you printing printer (it should be labeled \\printers\Follow you Printing\). To reinstall the printer driver, please open your Windows search tool (you can just hit the windows key on your keyboard and begin typing). Then type \\printers.ad.msoe.edu. You can then install the follow you printing driver (click on the one with spaces) by double clicking on it! Please let us know if this process works for you or if you have any other issues! Cheers, Austin Rovge (414) 277 7288 Submit a Ticket: helpdesk@msoe.edu Monday – Friday 8:00 AM – 4:30 PM Saturday and Sunday CLOSED

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Proxy Server Connections
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hi IT,
It seems with the Network upgrade in the Library our Proxy Server connection set-up was changed.
Currently, users on or off-campus are prompted to sign into Single Sign On when accessing our database links both on and off-campus.
Previously, when on-campus a user licked on our databases they would not be prompted to login into SSO. I believe the system just used IP authentication to verify that the user was allowed to access our resources.
This is the way we want access to the databases to work. On-campus users should not have to login into the Proxy Server via the SSO. Off-campus should have to log into the Proxy Server via the SSO.
Can you please fix this for us?
Thank you,
Denise Gergetz, MLIS Librarian II and Archivist Walter Schroeder Library, L201 Milwaukee School of Engineering 414-277-7182

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Assistance and Follow Up
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Good Morning:
We have put in several requests for problem situations in the bookstore over the last several weeks. We realize there have been updates on campus impacting service for some of our requests. We need an update so we can be operational to serve the campus community.
1. Printer is not functional at all. After three contacts the last we heard was it escalated to Ben Harris. We are processing book orders on the web and we do not want student info on the follow you printers. PLEASE ADVISE.
2. We have made several attempts to receive three replacement computers, which the latest schedule was scheduled for Monday, August 6 at 10am. Our files have been backed up and ready and we have not been contacted. I am now receiving the following error message upon log in:
The file c:\users\griesmaierAD\AppData Local Microsoft Office\Outlook\griesmaier@msoe. Griesmaier Kathleen.ost cannot be accessed.
It appears the EliteBook 8540w assigned to be is on it’s last leg. PLEASE HELP.
3. We requested a list of laptop charges so we could assist the campus community with an easy solution of lost or damaged cords. We were informed it was forwarded to a supervisor. What is the status of the list? It can take 7 – 10 business days for an order and we are getting closer to the start of the fall quarter. PLEASE ADVISE.
Thank you for your assistance and enjoy your day, Kathy Griesmaier Assistant Manager MSOE Bookstore 1025 North Broadway Milwaukee, WI 53202 griesmaier@msoe.edu<mailto:griesmaier@msoe.edu> ': 414/277-7173 6 :414/277-2898 SUMMER BOOKSTORE HOURS Monday- Thursday: 8am – 4:30pm Friday: 8am - 4:15pm CHECK OUT OUR WEBSITE AT www.bookstore.msoe.edu<http://www.bookstore.msoe.edu/> ACQUIRE OUR PRODUCTS ON OUR WEBSITE; EXPERIENCE OUR PRODUCT IN OUR STORE.

Dear Helpdesk,
I'm requesting an expedited review of my ticket regarding Adobe XD download error. This is a free download<https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adobe.com%2Fproducts%2Fxd.html&data=02%7C01%7C%7Ce7dd42047e5242d6c10c08d614f719e4%7C4046ceacfdd346c9ac80b7c4a49bab70%7C0%7C0%7C636719448844497316&sdata=1IjgTJT5Q62cwkXBHVbb7AByHCHQJsxPTxPZVZCbJXk%3D&reserved=0> from Adobe CC. helpdesk-note.body: I attempted to install Adobe Xd on three different users laptops (2 Dell 7390s, 1 HP x360) after uninstalling all adobe products including things like reader and the creative cloud, and went to the adobe site to try to and install Xd. When doing so, we reached 66% and the installation would say connection fail, and prompt to retry and then when you press retry it would continue to 81%, and at that point the same error would continue to pop up even if you hit retry. Would have to uninstall creative cloud after the install fails, so I'm curious if this is due to creative cloud installing and it not allowing Xd to continue installing correctly.
helpdesk-note.body-html: I attempted to install Adobe Xd on three different users laptops (2 Dell 7390s, 1 HP x360) after uninstalling all adobe products including things like reader and the creative cloud, and went to the adobe site to try to and install Xd. When doing so, we reached 66% and the installation would say connection fail, and prompt to retry and then when you press retry it would continue to 81%, and at that point the same error would continue to pop up even if you hit retry. Would have to uninstall creative cloud after the install fails, so I'm curious if this is due to creative cloud installing and it not allowing Xd to continue installing correctly.

helpdesk-note.body: Hi Dr. Nadezhda Shalamova, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/32981 I believe that we have fixed the issue with adobe XD. It appears the root cause was our configuration of adobe CC apps wasn't allowing XD to be install through the creative cloud app. It would install fine on computers without other adobe apps from us but it would not install on computers with our adobe packages. I created a package to fix the problem and deployed it to you and your students. Its called 'Adobe CC 2018 for students'. This is currently the only package that has been fixed other adobe products from software center currently have the same problem with XD. They will be updated over the next week to also have the fix applied. You should just be able to click install in software center on that 'Adobe CC 2018 for students' and it should just reinstall the products and fix the issue. Please let me know if anyone is still having the issue or if you have any questions. Thanks, Cameron Wilson Information Technology Dept Systems Admin 414-277-2625 wilsoncd@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.description: Hi, I am a Junior at Rufus King High School taking a class at MSOE and I was sent an email saying that I needed to upload an ID picture. To do this I need to be able to sign into the system with a user-id and a password. When I was given my course schedule for MSOE, I was given an id (583020), but I do not have a password. If you could help me with this, that would be great. Thanks, Lucille Steffes
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hi,
I am a Junior at Rufus King High School taking a class at MSOE and I was sent an email saying that I needed to upload an ID picture. To do this I need to be able to sign into the system with a user-id and a password. When I was given my course schedule for MSOE, I was given an id (583020), but I do not have a password. If you could help me with this, that would be great.
Thanks,
Lucille Steffes

helpdesk-note.body: Hi Lucy Steffes, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/32990 Thank you for contacting the IT helpdesk. You should be able to get your account information by accessing username.msoe.edu. The page will request your name and ID number, and then you will be given your username and will be shown the default password format. To change your password, register your account on pwdreg.msoe.edu using your current (the default) password. Then, you can visit pwd.msoe.edu to change the password. The ID photo can be uploaded on webcard.msoe.edu. Your login will be your username (no @msoe.edu) and your password. Please let us know if you are able to complete these steps and upload a photo! Respectfully, Amanda Goff 414.277.7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu Helpdesk Summer Hours: Monday-Friday 8 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Saturday-Sunday CLOSED "We are building a culture of exceptional customer service!"

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Meal Swipes Gone!
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hi IT,
My meal swipes were supposed to expire on the 15th of August; and I have attached a document detailing summer residence hall rules which state as such. Today when I attempted to process my purchases at Skylight cafe in the CC, I was unable to pay for anything and the worker at the cashier informed me that all of my swipes had expired. Expiring student's meal swipes two days before they are set to expire is a dishonest and unfair process, and I would request to speak with management if this is truly the case. If this is not the case and my missing swipes are the result of a technical issue, please restore my meal swipes to me. Due to the snafu if you could give me an extra day to spend the meals that I paid for (due to losing a day of purchasing power) I would very much appreciate it.
Thank You,
Grace Fleming
Forwarded Message:
Good Afternoon!
I would like to remind you of some important dates.
* The date for changing to your fall rooms is Friday, August 3rd to Sunday, August 5th. Your moves should be completed by Sunday evening, August 5th with your room key dropped off to the Johnson Hall mailroom by Sunday evening so that right away the next morning, custodial services will know your rooms are available to be cleaned and reconditioned for the next group of incoming students.
* If you are not planning on staying in the residence halls this fall, the deadline for moving out of the residence halls is Tuesday, August 1st.
There is a $25.00 per day charge for resident move-outs that occur past the date of August 1st.
* If you are staying in the residence halls this fall, we will be putting the keys to your fall rooms in your mailboxes on Friday, August 4th along with your room check-out form and an attached key return envelope. You’ll need to completely move to your fall rooms by Sunday, August 5thth and then return your room key and summer room condition report to the RWJ Mailroom by Sunday evening, August 5th.
* If your fall room is the same as your summer term room, then you do not need to move.
Other important things to note!
There will be a canine inspection for on Monday, August 13th. The inspections will start at approximately 7am. The canines will be accompanied by a handler and a member of the Public Safety Department. Please place any air deodorizers, scented candles or air fresheners in plastic bags and reduce the clutter in your room so the dogs will have access to the baseboards and corners of your room.
Summer meals: Any meals and meal dollars you have remaining on your meal plan from the spring term will remain on your account until August 15th. The meal plans for the fall term will be added to resident meal plan accounts on the afternoon of August 22nd.
Residence Hall Mail: Your mail will be switched to your fall rooms on August 6th.
Summer Move-out Checklist:
When you move out of your summer rooms, please be mindful of the following things.
£ Remove all personal items from your room. £ Clean your room (sweep/vacuum, dust). £ Take large items to the outside dumpsters. £ Remove all tape, posters, stickers and sticky tabs from the walls, floors, doors and furniture. £ All original furniture is in the room. £ All personal furniture removed. £ Turn off lights. £ Close windows £ Tell the Residence Life front desk of any repairs needed in the room. £ Clean your micro-fridge £ And make sure your room check-out form has been properly completed.
If you have any further questions about your summer housing, please let us know.
Thank you,
Jeanette Koch Residence Life Administrator Office: G2 Johnson Hall Phone: (414) 277-7402 kochj@msoe.edu

Forwarded Message:

Good Afternoon!
 
I would like to remind you of some important dates.
 
  • The date for changing to your fall rooms is Friday, August 3rd to Sunday, August 5th.   Your moves should be completed by Sunday evening, August 5th with your room key dropped off to the Johnson Hall mailroom by Sunday evening so that right away the next morning, custodial services will know your rooms are available to be cleaned and reconditioned for the next group of incoming students.
 
    • If you are not planning on staying in the residence halls this fall, the deadline for moving out of the residence halls is Tuesday, August 1st. 
 
                             There is a $25.00 per day charge for resident move-outs that occur past the date of August 1st. 
 
    • If you are staying in the residence halls this fall, we will be putting the keys to your fall rooms in your mailboxes on Friday, August 4th along with your room check-out form and an attached key return envelope.  You’ll need to completely move to your fall rooms by Sunday, August 5thth and then return your room key and summer room condition report to the RWJ Mailroom by Sunday evening, August 5th. 
 
  • If your fall room is the same as your summer term room, then you do not need to move. 
 
Other important things to note!
 
There will be a canine inspection for on Monday, August 13th.  
The inspections will start at approximately 7am. The canines will be accompanied by a handler and a member of the Public Safety Department. Please place any air deodorizers, scented candles or air fresheners in plastic bags and reduce the clutter in your room so the dogs will have access to the baseboards and corners of your room. 
 
Summer meals: 
Any meals and meal dollars you have remaining on your meal plan from the spring term will remain on your account until August 15th.  The meal plans for the fall term will be added to resident meal plan accounts on the afternoon of August 22nd.
 
Residence Hall Mail:
Your mail will be switched to your fall rooms on August 6th. 
 
Summer Move-out Checklist:
 
When you move out of your summer rooms, please be mindful of the following things.
£  Remove all personal items from your room.
£  Clean your room (sweep/vacuum, dust).
£  Take large items to the outside dumpsters.
£  Remove all tape, posters, stickers and sticky tabs from the walls, floors, doors and furniture.
£  All original furniture is in the room.
£  All personal furniture removed.
£  Turn off lights.
£  Close windows
£  Tell the Residence Life front desk of any repairs needed in the room.
£  Clean your micro-fridge
£  And make sure your room check-out form has been properly completed.
 
If you have any further questions about your summer housing, please let us know. 
 
Thank you,
 
Jeanette Koch
Residence Life Administrator
Office: G2 Johnson Hall
Phone: (414) 277-7402
kochj@msoe.edu
